The Oldsmobile Six was built from the 1920s until the 1940s. It was known as the Model 30, Model 57 and the Model 37 during the time it was built in [[Lansing, Michigan]]. General Motors used the [[GM B platform|General Motors B platform]], shared with the [[Buick Master Six]]. 

